            <h2>Jagat Mandir</h2>






<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," >
            <p>
         

                The Dwarkadhish Temple, also known as Jagat Mandir, is a significant Hindu temple in Dwarka, Gujarat, dedicated to Lord Krishna. It is one of the four key destinations in the Char Dham pilgrimage. 
Information about the Dwarkadhish Temple (Jagat Mandir) includes that the main shrine has five stories and is supported by 72 pillars. The temple has two main entrances: the Moksha Dwara and the Swarga Dwara. It is one of the 108 Divya Desams, or holy abodes of Vishnu. For more facts about the temple, you can refer to Times of India. 

</p>
